text: "I Just Don't Know What to Do with Myself" is a song written by Burt Bacharach and Hal David. The most popular version is the Dusty Springfield 1964 single. It was taken from her second studio album Dusty. It went to number 16 in Australia, number 5 in Ireland and the Netherlands and number 3 in New Zealand and the United Kingdom. ==Dionne Warwick version== In 1966, Dionne Warwick released "I Just Don't Know What to Do with Myself" for her sixth studio album Here Where There Is Love. It went to number 26 in the United States and number 36 in Canada. It was later covered by Marcia Hines in 1976 and The White Stripes in 2003.
